    "summary": "I started travelling before I learnt how to walk. \n\nMy life\u2019s been always dynamic, a lot of moving from one country to another was involved and, still, I can\u2019t get enough of it. I understood that being able to connect with people through the same language was the key against hectic and, sometimes, isolated reality.\n\nIn the past 15 years, I pursued a professional translator career, pushing myself out of the comfort zone by living abroad to sharpen my language skills and, most importantly, to gain a deepened understanding of other cultures. \n\nWords are a powerful tool. And I get enthusiastic when it comes to translation, ergo making intercultural communication possible for a variety of domains: my best-loved include IT sphere, AI, face analysis software, DOOH and programmatic Advertising. I'm familiar with the specific language of this field thanks to my working experience in Amsterdam - a world-leading hub in Artificial Intelligence technologies. Business (legal) domain is my other favourite where I excel. A specialisation I grasped during my Master\u2019s degree studies in Italy. \n\nWith my international experience, from Russia to Italy, from the UK to the Netherlands, I learnt to identify the core message of my client and to transform it into a tailored-to-the-right-audinece translated content.\n\n\n\ud83c\udf0d What languages do I work with?\nI translate from Russian, English and Spanish into Italian\n\n\n\ud83d\udd0d Are you looking for a professional translator?\n\u25aa A bachelor\u2019s degree holder in translation \ud83c\udf93 and \n\u25aa completing a master\u2019s degree in Languages for Communication in International Enterprises and Companies \n\u25aa SDL Trados user\n\u25aa get the job done mindset\n\n\n\ud83d\udccc What are the areas of specialisation?\n\u25aa IT (face recognition and face analysis software, programmatic adv)\n\u25aa business domain\n\u25aa legal (contracts)\n\u25aa marketing material (website localisation, blog, newsletter, PR)\n\nDo you need a translation that does not fall under any of these categories? Just ask me and I\u2019ll let you know whether I can help you with a particular project. \n\n\nVisit my website www.pitchperfect.studio or contact me on \ud83d\udce9 liudmila@pitchperfect.studio",
